casebody.data:
Dwayne M. WILLIAMS, Appellant,
v.
The STATE of Florida, Appellee. No. 3D19-369 District Court of Appeal of Florida, Third District. Opinion filed April 17, 2019 Dwayne M. Williams, in proper person. Ashley Moody, Attorney General, for appellee. Before FERNANDEZ, LOGUE, and MILLER, JJ. PER CURIAM.

Affirmed. See State v. Enmund , 476 So.2d 165 , 166 (Fla. 1985) ("[A] defendant can be convicted of and sentenced for both felony murder and the underlying felony.").
